2200344c-5e37-4455-a3ca-90892e736eda.05788c12-efa3-468f-9fb6-16f6991d0291.description=
This operation does not do anything. It can be used to filter flow variables by defining them as inputs and filtering them in the Results tab.

Inputs\:
    field1 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field2 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field3 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field4 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the value of  "field1" as it was specified at input or when filtered. 

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
2200344c-5e37-4455-a3ca-90892e736eda.05788c12-efa3-468f-9fb6-16f6991d0291.prompt=${failedFiles} 2200344c-5e37-4455-a3ca-90892e736eda.33c5136c-9229-4b30-baca-cfc34123835c.prompt=Where are the Content Packs stored? 2200344c-5e37-4455-a3ca-90892e736eda.5d9efecb-169f-4067-8a1e-a3058fa64c95.description=
FSRename changes the name of a file.  This operation will not move a file to a different directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The file to rename, including directory.
newName - The new name of the file, NOT INCLUDING DIRECTORY.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host for this operation.
password - Password for the user.
overwrite - If false the operation will fail if newName exists (true, false).

Responses\:
failure - The rename failed.
success - The rename succeeded.

2200344c-5e37-4455-a3ca-90892e736eda.6be120e4-766d-4aaf-b9f8-3f3b604ff647.description=
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.

2200344c-5e37-4455-a3ca-90892e736eda.b0514d6c-c8ce-4958-a6a1-51962fa95021.description=
Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - The directory to check.
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
user - Username to use for thread impersonation on the RAS host when reading.
password - Password for the user.

Returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - The number of children.

Responses\:
failure - The operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success - The operation succeeded.

 Extract a ZIP archive.

Inputs\:
zipFileName - The absolute path including file name of the ZIP file that wants to be extracted. 
outputDirectory - Location where the extracted content to be written. If the directory doesn't exist, will be created.


Responses\:
success - The files were extracted successfully.
failure - The files could not be extracted.
